<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
2.5-2.55 mm long (mean = 2.51 mm; n = 4); 2.27-2.55
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. This species is distinguished by the protibiae posterior faces flat, unarmed; antennal club as broad as tall; posterolateral carina oblique, granulate; elytral disc flat, without a transverse depression; elytral striae weakly impressed; elytral interstriae with one row of dominant tubercles.
</paragraph>
